Sentencas: The role of a SnO2-samarium doped ceria (SDC) additional anode layer in a direct carbon fuel cell (DCFC) with SDC-(Li0.67Na0.33)(2)CO3 composite electrolyte and lithiated NiO-SDC-(Li0.67Na0.33)(2)CO3 composite cathode is investigated and compared with a NiO-SDC extra anode layer.
Titulo: A SnO2-samarium doped ceria additional anode layer in a direct carbon fuel cell

Sentencas: Catalytic grown carbon fiber mixed with (Li0.67Na0.33)(2)CO3 is used as a fuel.
Titulo: A SnO2-samarium doped ceria additional anode layer in a direct carbon fuel cell

Sentencas: At 750 degrees C, the maximum power outputs of 192 and 143 mW cm-(2) are obtained by the cells with SnO2-SDC and NiO-SDC layers, respectively.
Titulo: A SnO2-samarium doped ceria additional anode layer in a direct carbon fuel cell

Sentencas: In the SnO2-SDC layer, the reduction of SnO2 and the oxidation of Sn happen simultaneously during the cell operation, and the Sn/SnO2 redox cycle provides an additional route for fuel conversion.
Titulo: A SnO2-samarium doped ceria additional anode layer in a direct carbon fuel cell

Sentencas: The formation of an insulating dense interlayer between the anode and electrolyte layers, which usually happens in DCFCs with metal anodes, is avoided in the cell with the SnO2-SDC layer, and the stability of the cell is improved consequently.
Titulo: A SnO2-samarium doped ceria additional anode layer in a direct carbon fuel cell
